        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 7. From the left: Oxynoemacheilus seyhanicola, HUIC SEY-1, holotype, 40.3 mm SL; Turkey: Dam bridge near Adana; Oxynoemacheilus sarus, FSJF 2327, 49.6 mm SL; Turkey: Turkey: lower stream Çakıt; Oxynoemacheilus seyhanicola, FSJF 2959, 45.9 mm SL; Turkey: stream tributary to stream Kirksu. Red rectangle indicates the position of black blotches in HUIC SEY-1. Red ovals indicate black blotches in O. sarus. Black line indicate the posterior end of the hypural complex." ;
